OL,3,CSecretary of State challenged to take
OL,4,Cpart in 'heavy lifting' to reform
OL,5,CStormont
OL,7,F"But it is a warning against
OL,8,Fcomplacency that neither the First or
OL,9,FDeputy First Minister would give a
OL,10,Ffirm commitment when called upon to do
OL,11,Fso that they would not use the power
OL,12,Fto collapse the Executive again.
OL,14,F"The only possible reason for those
OL,15,Fparties to argue that they should
OL,16,Fretain the power to collapse the
OL,17,Finstitution is if they intend to
OL,18,Feither use that power or use the
OL,19,Fthreat of using it to control the
OL,20,FExecutive.
